.NET Framework 3.5.name: OVRPlayerController
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: Controls the player's movement in virtual reality.

fields.name: BackAndSideDampen
fields.summary: The rate of additional damping when moving sideways or backwards.

fields.name: CameraHeight
fields.summary: The CameraHeight is the actual height of the HMD and can be used to adjust the height of the character controller, which will affect the ability of the character to move into areas with a low ceiling.

fields.name: EnableLinearMovement
fields.summary: When true, user input will be applied to linear movement. Set this to false whenever the player controller needs to ignore input for linear movement.

fields.name: EnableRotation
fields.summary: When true, user input will be applied to rotation. Set this to false whenever the player controller needs to ignore input for rotation.

fields.name: FixedSpeedSteps
fields.summary: How many fixed speeds to use with linear movement? 0=linear control

fields.name: HmdResetsY
fields.summary: If true, reset the initial yaw of the player controller when the Hmd pose is recentered.

fields.name: HmdRotatesY
fields.summary: If true, tracking data from a child OVRCameraRig will update the direction of movement.

fields.name: JumpForce
fields.summary: The force applied to the character when jumping.

fields.name: RotationAmount
fields.summary: The rate of rotation when using a gamepad.

fields.name: RotationRatchet
fields.summary: The rate of rotation when using the keyboard.

fields.name: SnapRotation
fields.summary: The player will rotate in fixed steps if Snap Rotation is enabled.

fields.name: Teleported
fields.summary: This bool is set to true whenever the player controller has been teleported. It is reset after every frame. Some systems, such as CharacterCameraConstraint, test this boolean in order to disable logic that moves the character controller immediately following the teleport.

fields.name: useProfileData
fields.summary: If true, each OVRPlayerController will use the player's physical height.

methods.name: ResetOrientation()
methods.summary: Resets the player look rotation when the device orientation is reset.

methods.name: UpdateMovement()
UpdateTransform(OVRCameraRig rig)
methods.summary: Invoked by OVRCameraRig's UpdatedAnchors callback. Allows the Hmd rotation to update the facing direction of the player.

events.name: CameraUpdated
events.summary: This event is raised immediately after the camera transform has been updated, but before movement is updated.

events.name: PreCharacterMove
events.summary: This event is raised right before the character controller is actually moved in order to provide other systems the opportunity to move the character controller in response to things other than user input, such as movement of the HMD. See CharacterCameraConstraint.cs for an example of this.

events.name: TransformUpdated
events.summary: This event is raised after the character controller is moved. This is used by the OVRAvatarLocomotion script to keep the avatar transform synchronized with the OVRPlayerController.
